Adult male.description: Ruby-crowned Kinglets have an eyering whereas Golden-crowned Kinglets have black-and-white stripes on their faces. If visible, adult males have a bright red (not golden) crown.

Adult.description: Ruby-crowned Kinglets have an eyering unlike Golden-crowned Kinglets, which have black-and-white stripes on the face. They also have buffy flanks whereas Golden-crowned have grayish flanks.

Adult/immature.description: Brown Creepers don’t look much like Golden-crowned Kinglets, but their habitat and calls are similar. Kinglet calls are usually slightly shorter and repeated several times, while Brown Creeper calls are longer, descend slightly, and waver a bit.
